(20, 1, '2017-03-27 17:13:36', '2017-03-27 17:13:36', 'Gyumri has all the chances for further development.\r\n\r\nMinister of Justice Arpine Hovhannisyan, who is on the ruling Republican Party of Armenia (RPA) proportional representation list for the forthcoming parliamentary election in the country, on Sunday stated the abovementioned at the RPA election campaign town hall with voters in Gyumri, the second largest city of Armenia.\r\n\r\n“I have faith that this town has all the chances to become the center of the world,” she added.\r\n\r\nAlso, she urged Gyumri residents to vote on election day on April 2, and make the right choice, not forgetting about the days to come.\r\n\r\nThe RPA on Sunday is campaigning in Shirak Province, ahead of the National Assembly election.\r\n\r\n<iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/SIKcPXHi2Iw" width="560" height="315" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe>', 'Armenia official: Gyumri can become center of the world', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'armenia-official-gyumri-can-become-center-of-the-world', '', '', '2017-03-28 19:19:33', '2017-03-28 19:19:33', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8080/finish%20work/?p=20', 0, 'post', '', 0),
