(132, 1, '2017-03-29 16:04:41', '2017-03-29 16:04:41', '<div class="fl-page-content">\r\n<div class="fl-content-full container">\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="fl-content col-md-12"><article id="fl-post-2345" class="fl-post post-2345 page type-page status-publish hentry">\r\n<div class="fl-post-content clearfix">\r\n<div class="vc_row wpb_row vc_row-fluid">\r\n<div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-12">\r\n<div class="vc_column-inner ">\r\n<div class="wpb_wrapper">\r\n<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element  section-text">\r\n<div class="wpb_wrapper">\r\n\r\nAlexandrapol-Gyumri has been famous not only for its craftsmen, men of arts and cultural values but also for its churches. People used to  call Gyumri “The Town of Seven Churches”. The local people have a special devotion to churches. In his famous song “Eyed the Wits” bard Jivani characterized the love of the Gyumri people towards churches. In fact, seven churches were built in Gyumri, among them four Armenian Apostolic churches, a Russian, a Greek and Catholic churches.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="vc_grid-container-wrapper vc_clearfix"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="vc_row wpb_row vc_row-fluid vc_custom_1464190452607 vc_row-has-fill vc_row-no-padding" data-vc-full-width="true" data-vc-full-width-init="true" data-vc-stretch-content="true"></div>\r\n<div class="vc_row-full-width vc_clearfix"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</article></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<footer class="fl-page-footer-wrap">\r\n<div class="fl-page-footer"></div>\r\n</footer>', 'Churches', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'churches', '', '', '2017-03-29 20:28:46', '2017-03-29 20:28:46', '', 126, 'http://localhost:8080/finish%20work/?page_id=132', 0, 'page', '', 0),
